Getting started - The CHICKEN Scheme wiki https://wiki.call-cc.org/man/5/Getting started
Getting started. CHICKEN is a compiler that translates Scheme source files into C, which in turn can be fed to a C compiler to generate a standalone executable. An interpreter is also available and can be used as a scripting environment or for testing programs before compilation. This chapter is designed to get you started with CHICKEN &hellip;
